  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6758.4 sitting in the thick negative gamma zone between 6745-6755 (all showing massive -8B+ amplifying flows), dealers are forced to chase momentum—selling into any rally and buying any dip, creating unstable price action. The regime flip into PIN territory combined with the wall break and GEX surge indicates dealers just shifted positioning, but spot remains dangerously close to the 6745 max negative gamma strike where dealer selling pressure peaks. Key inflection points are 6720 (GEX flip) as downside support and 6775 (max positive gamma) as the critical upside level where dealer behavior shifts from amplifying to stabilizing.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile whipsaw action until SPX either breaks below 6720 or rallies above 6775.",
